 Abhängigkeit von der Perspektive, aus der man ihn betrachtet, seine Gestalt verändert.Die Beiträge des Bandes widmen sich dieser Vielgestaltigkeit an der Schnittstelle verschiedener Disziplinen.  aIn recent years in the German-speaking world, the audiobook has gained in popularity and significance. One can scarcely imagine libraries and bookstores without them - and academic research is also showing a growing interest. At the same time, it is a phenomenon which needs to be outlined in more detail. As the word audiobook already implies, it is a multifaceted object, which not only addresses various senses at the same time, but also changes form depending on our vantage point. The essays in this volume focus on this polymorphic quality, at the interface of various disciplines.  afunded by OGeSoMo  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAudiobooksvCongresses. 0aDictionvCongresses. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticism. 0aVoice culturevCongresses. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aHören. 4aHörspiel. 4aKlang. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aMündlichkeit. 4aSound. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aHearing.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia.  aOral Language.  aRadio Play.  aSound.1 aBenthien, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernhart, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBung, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBung, Stephanie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1